    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "\"endianness\" is a property determined by context, not a transformation you can apply like you are suggesting with `fork_data_root` as `563412`\r\n\r\nin the context of generating a signature domain, the \"endianness\" doesn't really matter and like @hwwhww is saying we just concatenate the bytes here\r\n\r\nif you look in the spec where we use `ENDIANNESS` you can see where it is relevant: mapping from integers to bytes and back\r\n\r\n\r\ngoing to close this issue as it doesn't have a relevant change; feel free to re-open if you have another point to make :)",
