    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@ralexstokes I understand `ENDIANNESS` is for mapping integers to bytes and back. \r\n\r\nI am saying that right now the spec is saying to append `domain_type` bytes to the front of the byte array. If `domain_type` is `[0, 0]` then when you convert the bytes to an integer in little endian this has the effect of multiplying by `2 ** 16`. \r\n\r\nHowever I think the effect that actually happens on-chain is to \"do nothing\". This means you should be appending `domain_type` bytes to the **end** of the byte array. ",
